1.1 Usage from Elisp
====================

To set env variables defined in ‘~/.env/foo’:

     (setenv-file (expand-file-name "~/.env/foo"))

   Or, if you have a string instead of a file:

     (setenv-file-str "FOO=foo\nBAR=bar")


