1.2 Usage from org-mode
=======================

The example below shows a convenient way to declare and set environment
variables in an ‘org’ document:

     #+NAME: env
     | Var  | Value           |
     |------+-----------------|
     | FOO  | ~/foo           |
     | BAR  | $FOO/bar        |
     | ОФИС | ДОМ             |
     | BAZ  | nosubst:FOO$BAR |

     #+begin_src emacs-lisp :var env=env
       (setenv-file-set-pairs env)
     #+end_src


